title: Hack Is Wack! (2010)
Ask HN: Will the government be able to block CBDC transactions of individuals?
text:
I was watching an "interview" conducted by a politician from the UK, Nigel Farage. He was interviewing a cryptocurrency enthusiast about the Bank of England's CBDC(Central Bank Digital Currency) the "Britcoin". In that interview he said that the government would be able to block individuals from using the digital currency and that gives more control to the government on individuals.

Is this a valid point? If yes, then how is it possible with CBDC?
